ollo-Soyuz Test Project Facts, Part C (1975)}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=history_of_space_travel_13_apollo_soyuz|name=History of Space Travel, Episode 13: The Mission of Apollo-Soyuz}}\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=CMP_249_Our_Laboratories_in_Space_Episode7.wmv|name=CMP_249_Our_Laboratories_in_Space_Episode7.wmv}} (several types of media formats are available)\n* {{Internet Archive short film|id=Jsc-603Apollo17-OnTheShouldersOfGiants.wmv|name=https://archive.org/details/Jsc-603Apollo17-OnTheShouldersOfGiants.wmv}} (several types of media formats are available)\n\n{{Soyuz}}\n{{Apollo program}}\n{{Russian space program}}\n{{NASA navbox}}\n{{Orbital launches in 1975}}\n\n{{Use American English|date=March 2019}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Apollo-Soyuz Test Project}}\n[[Category:Apollo\u2013Soyuz Test Project| ]]\n[[Category:1975 in international relations]]\n[[Category:1975 in the Soviet Union]]\n[[Category:Apollo program]]\n[[Category:Crewed Soyuz missions]]\n[[Category:Soviet Union\u2013United States relations]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched in 1975]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft which reentered in 1975]]\n[[Category:July 1975 events]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched by Soyuz-U rockets]]\n[[Category:Spacecraft launched by Saturn rockets]]\n[[Category:Alexei Leonov]]\n[[Category:Thomas P. Stafford]]\n[[Category:Deke Slayton]]\n", "name_user": "Netoholic", "label": "safe", "comment": "post-move link fix", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Apollo%E2%80%93Soyuz_Test_Project"}
